<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-331-509  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 331 509.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Systems News  Feb 5 1990 n453 p19(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>It's not what you say; to sell abroad, the easy part is switchinglanguages. (Viewpoint) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Hurd, John.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Demand for software products is growing faster internationallythan in the US, but marketing products abroad is expensive andmore complex than simply translating materials.andP;  The mostimportant step is to determine if the product can be translated.andO;Translatable software needs an architecture that separates whatthe user sees from what the code does, so that the code will notbe disturbed if the program is translated.andP;  Other concerns arecharacter sets over eight bits of memory, multiple character sets,data and time routines.andP;  Software for the Middle East requires notonly completely different character sets of more than eight bitsof memory, but also the ability to print in multiple directions.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Ticker:    DEC.andO;Topic:     Software PublishersSalesInternationalGrowthCostMiddle EastProduct DevelopmentSoftware ModificationCharacter Sets.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>